      "text": "ISM Marketplace - Hyperlane Docs\n[Skip to main content] \n[Hyperlane Docshome page![light logo]![dark logo]] \nSearch...\n⌘K\nSearch...\nNavigation\nModular Security\nISM Marketplace\n[Home\n] [Learn\n] [Agent Operators\n] \n##### Introduction\n* [\nProtocol Overview\n] \n##### Protocol\n* General Message Passing\n* Modular Security\n* [\nISM Overview\n] \n* [\nSequence Diagram\n] \n* [\nISM Marketplace\n] \n* [\nCreate Your Own ISM\n] \n* Standard ISMs\n* Economic Security\n* Hyperlane Agents\n##### HYPER and Protocol Economics\n* [\nHyperlane Protocol Economics\n] \n##### Reference\n* Send &amp; Receive\n* Post-Dispatch Hooks\n##### Alt-VM Implementations &amp; Guides\n* [\nAlt-VM Implementations\n] \n* [\nImplementation Guide\n] \n* [\nCosmos SDK Module\n] \n##### Resources\n* [\nMessage Debugging\n] \n* [\nGlossary\n] \n* [\nFrequently Asked Questions\n] \n* [\nAudits\n] \nOn this page\n* [Standard ISMs] \n* [Community ISMs] \nModular Security\n# ISM Marketplace\nCopy page\nCopy page\nThe ISM Marketplace is a registry of Interchain Security Modules (I",
      "highlights": [
        "ular Security\nISM Marketplace\n[Home\n] [Learn\n] [Agent Operators\n] \n##### Introduction\n* [ Protocol Overview\n] \n##### Protocol\n* General Message Passing\n* Modular Security\n* [\nISM Overview\n] \n* [ Sequence Diagram\n] \n* [\nISM Marketplace\n] \n* [\nCreate Your Own ISM\n] \n* Standard ISMs\n* Economic Security * Hyperlane Agents\n##### HYPER and Protocol Economics\n* [\nHyperlane Protocol Economics\n] \n##### Reference * Send & Receive\n* Post-Dispatch Hooks\n##### Alt-VM Implementations & Guides\n* [\nAlt-VM Implementations\n] \n* [ Implementation Guide\n] \n* [\nCosmos SDK Module\n] \n##### Resources\n* [\nMessage Debugging\n] \n* [\nGlossary\n] \n* [ Frequently Asked Questions\n] \n* [\nAudits\n] \nOn this page\n* [Standard ISMs] \n* [Community ISMs] \nModular Security # ISM Marketplace\nCopy page\nCopy page The ISM Marketplace is a registry of Interchain Security Modules (ISMs) that lets developers customize how their messages are verified. Application teams can choose ISMs based on their security, latency, and cost requirements (i.e., using stricter verification for high-value messages and lighter ISMs for routine transfers).The marketplace includes both standard ISMs from Abacus Works, and community-contributed ISMs developed by partner teams and community members.### [​ ] \nStandard ISMs\nStandard ISMs are developed and maintained by Abacus Works.\n|ISM Name|Type|Stage|Description| [Aggregation ISM (Static)] |Composition|In Production|Combines multiple ISMs together, requiring all or a k‑of‑n subset ... * Static variants are immutable in bytecode.\n* Storage variants keep module sets and thresholds mutable in state. ### [​\n] \nCommunity ISMs\nCommunity ISMs are developed and maintained by contributors outside Abacus Works. ... Noble ISM|Security|In Development|\nPolygon zkEVM V2 ISM|Security|In Development| ... Wormhole ISM|Security|In Development|\nWas this page helpful?\nYesNo\n[Sequence Diagram] [Create Your Own ISM]"
